---
source: crates/wxctl/src/output/discovery_snapshots_test.rs
expression: "explain_presto(&panel(100, ColorMode::Plain, GlyphSet::Ascii))"
---

  presto_engine   watsonx.data - saas, software
  id field - id

  | Endpoints
    create   POST     /v3/presto_engines
    get      GET      /v3/presto_engines/{id}
    list     GET      /v3/presto_engines?limit=100
    update   PATCH    /v3/presto_engines/{id}
    delete   DELETE   /v3/presto_engines/{id}

  | Fields   (required first)
    display_name          string          required            Body
    origin                string          required            Body
    configuration         object          required   locked   Body
    description           string          optional            Body
    associated_catalogs   array<string>   optional            Body
    tags                  array<string>   optional            Body
    status                string          optional            Body
    id                    string          computed   locked   Computed
    external_host_name    string          computed   locked   Computed
    host_name             string          computed   locked   Computed

  | Dependencies
    associated_catalogs  -->  ${storage_registration.<ref_name>}   optional
    associated_catalogs  -->  ${database_registration.<ref_name>}   optional

  | Authoring
    envelope   A config is one or more YAML documents separated by `---`. Each has top-level `kind` and `ref_name`, then the fields below at the top level (not nested under `spec`).
    ref_name   Unique handle for this resource within the config. Used to reference it from other resources, then stripped before the API call (not a schema field).
    reference  Reference another resource by its ref_name: `${<kind>.<ref_name>}` resolves to its id, `${<kind>.<ref_name>.<field>}` to a specific field. Values resolve late, at plan/apply time.
